                    <title>I don&#039;t usually stream twitte…</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:Comment:7764"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2012-01-26:6456126:Comment:7764</id>
                                        <updated>2012-01-26T08:13:05.877Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>corey haines</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/128952ghvkcvj</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t usually stream twitter on the screen, as I haven&#039;t seen a lot of traffic during events. As Xavier said, it might also be a bit of a distraction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, feel free to try it. Pay attention to how much people focus on it and report back. :) You can always take it down if it becomes too much of a distraction during the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have fun on Saturday!&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t usually stream twitter on the screen, as I haven&#039;t seen a lot of traffic during events. As Xavier said, it might also be a bit of a distraction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, feel free to try it. Pay attention to how much people focus on it and report back. :) You can always take it down if it becomes too much of a distraction during the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have fun on Saturday!&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
